I'll be happy to answer questions about the deck and please do give any suggestions.

deck_description: A deck focuse on the 3 new cards dawn, dusk and sky

Maliss coming to Master Duel with full support, no pre-hits, and Apollousa still in the format. Clearly, the game is balanced exactly as John Konami intended. This list is pretty straight forward as far as the deckbuilding goes, with a side deck included for cards I've been considering swapping in. Lancea for the mirror, Allure for more draw power and banish value, and TB to help extend hands of "Normal White Rabbit" further. So far though, I've been enjoying the deck as-is. TB-11 and Allure open up more vulnerablities to Ash and Droll. With Lancea, I would likely swap them in for the Imperms, but losing a decent negate when going second for a dead card against most other decks doesn't feel great. Weigh the pros and cons as you will.

deck_excerpt: CAN WE SYNCHRO IN A MALISS WONDERLAND? Most definitely!
deck_description:
CAN WE SYNCHRO IN A MALISS WONDERLAND? Most definitely!

Better yet, can we play a deck that doesn't care about the increasingly popular Lancea, Chaos Hunter and Fuwalos! Most definitely! White Forest is well-positioned to compete in a meta dominated by Maliss, but the usual cards that threaten White Forest like Droll and Lockbird, Dimension Shifter and Bystials are hardly present! Made up of a incredible FOUR complimentary engines, (Sinful Spoils, Azamina, Millennium and Fiendsmith) White Forest is certainly a force to be reckoned with in the 2025 meta that will catch many duelists on Masterduel ladder off guard! 


Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!
